    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-11T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-11T21:00:00-05:00" n="67"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d67">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 E.W./5–1245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-12T09:00:00+07:00"
                            >May 12, 1945—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 1:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>773. As the Department will note (my telegram 772, May 12<note n="37"
                        xml:id="d67fn37">Not printed.</note>), the Generalissimo in his V–E<note
                        n="38" xml:id="d67fn38">Victory—Europe, May 8, when German armies
                        surrendered.</note> Day address delivered at a reception attended by the
                    Diplomatic Corps and highest officials of the National Government stressed: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Tribute to U. S. S. R., Britain and United States for victory in the
                            West,</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Tribute to President Roosevelt and</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Rededication of Chinese Government and people to the task of defeating
                            Japan.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>This address was extremely well received and should have excellent effect.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hurley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
